This PR makes the following fixes in the filestore:

* `indexCacheBuf` no longer tries to correct `fseq`, since the head hole-filling should have already identified the gap;
* `writeMsgRecordLocked` now only replaces the cache `fseq` if writing the first index;
* An off-by-one error in tail hole-filling that could mark one sequence as incorrectly deleted and altogether miss the last one has been fixed;
* Skip messages are now written without releasing and re-acquiring the message block mutex.

Signed-off-by: Neil Twigg <neil@nats.io>

